@desc How to determine which version of GNOME is running.

You can determine the version of GNOME that is running on your system by
going to the $gui(Details) panel in $gui(Settings).

[steps]
* Open the $Activities; overview and start typing $gui(Details).

* Click on $gui(Details) to open the panel.

  A window appears showing information about your system, including your
  distributionâ€™s name and the GNOME version.
